Name:         Basic bit/byte converter
Description:  A simple script to convert bit or byte values
              between simple unprefixed numbers and
              human-readable prefixed forms
              (eg. 235235235 vs 224.3M)
Author:       Tony Yarusso <tonyyarusso@gmail.com>
Copyright:    2013, Tony Yarusso
License:      BSD 3-clause
              <http://opensource.org/licenses/BSD-3-Clause>

Usage: bitconvert.py -p|-s <value>
e.g. bitconvert.py -p 235235235

Options:
 -h, --help
       Print help screen
 -p, --prefixed
       Convert from simple input to prefixed human-readable output
 -s, --simple
       Convert from prefixed human-readable input to simple output
